events.description: Vespasian is proclaimed Emperor of Rome; his predecessor, Vitellius, attempts to abdicate but is captured and killed at the Gemonian stairs.
events.html: • AD 69 – Vespasian is proclaimed Emperor of Rome; his predecessor, Vitellius, attempts to abdicate but is captured and killed at the Gemonian stairs.[1]

events.description: Pope Innocent I is elected, the only pope to succeed his father in the office.
events.html: • 401 – Pope Innocent I is elected, the only pope to succeed his father in the office.[2]

events.description: Damghan earthquake: An earthquake near the Persian city of Damghan kills an estimated 200,000 people, the sixth deadliest earthquake in recorded history.
events.html: • 856 – Damghan earthquake: An earthquake near the Persian city of Damghan kills an estimated 200,000 people, the sixth deadliest earthquake in recorded history.[3]

events.description: Luoyang, eastern capital of the Tang dynasty, is captured by rebel leader Huang Chao during the reign of Emperor Xizong.
events.html: • 880 – Luoyang, eastern capital of the Tang dynasty, is captured by rebel leader Huang Chao during the reign of Emperor Xizong.[4]

events.description: Three weeks after the death of King Henry I of England, Stephen of Blois claims the throne and is privately crowned King of England, beginning the English Anarchy.
events.html: • 1135 – Three weeks after the death of King Henry I of England, Stephen of Blois claims the throne and is privately crowned King of England, beginning the English Anarchy.[5]

events.description: Pope Honorius III approves the Dominican Order through the papal bull of confirmation Religiosam vitam.
events.html: • 1216 – Pope Honorius III approves the Dominican Order through the papal bull of confirmation Religiosam vitam.[6]

events.description: The forces of the Catholic Monarchs, Ferdinand and Isabella, take control of Almería from the Nasrid ruler of Granada, Muhammad XIII.
events.html: • 1489 – The forces of the Catholic Monarchs, Ferdinand and Isabella, take control of Almería from the Nasrid ruler of Granada, Muhammad XIII.[7]

events.description: Sino-Burmese War: The war ends with the Qing dynasty withdrawing from Burma forever.
events.html: • 1769 – Sino-Burmese War: The war ends with the Qing dynasty withdrawing from Burma forever.[8]

events.description: Nguyễn Huệ proclaims himself Emperor Quang Trung, in effect abolishing on his own the Lê dynasty.
events.html: • 1788 – Nguyễn Huệ proclaims himself Emperor Quang Trung, in effect abolishing on his own the Lê dynasty.[9]

events.description: The Turkish fortress of Izmail is stormed and captured by Alexander Suvorov and his Russian armies.
events.html: • 1790 – The Turkish fortress of Izmail is stormed and captured by Alexander Suvorov and his Russian armies.[10]

events.description: The Embargo Act, forbidding trade with all foreign countries, is passed by the U.S. Congress at the urging of President Thomas Jefferson.
events.html: • 1807 – The Embargo Act, forbidding trade with all foreign countries, is passed by the U.S. Congress at the urging of President Thomas Jefferson.[11]

events.description: Ludwig van Beethoven conducts and performs in concert at the Theater an der Wien, Vienna, with the premiere of his Fifth Symphony, Sixth Symphony, Fourth Piano Concerto and Choral Fantasy.
events.html: • 1808 – Ludwig van Beethoven conducts and performs in concert at the Theater an der Wien, Vienna, with the premiere of his Fifth Symphony, Sixth Symphony, Fourth Piano Concerto and Choral Fantasy.[12]

events.description: India's first freight train is operated in Roorkee, to transport material for the construction of the Ganges Canal.
events.html: • 1851 – India's first freight train is operated in Roorkee, to transport material for the construction of the Ganges Canal.[13]

events.description: The Library of Congress in Washington, D.C., burns.
events.html: • 1851 – The Library of Congress in Washington, D.C., burns.[14]

events.description: American Civil War: Savannah, Georgia, falls to the Union's Army of the Tennessee, and General Sherman tells President Abraham Lincoln: "I beg to present you as a Christmas gift the city of Savannah".
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: Savannah, Georgia, falls to the Union's Army of the Tennessee, and General Sherman tells President Abraham Lincoln: "I beg to present you as a Christmas gift the city of Savannah".[15]

events.description: Itō Hirobumi, a samurai, becomes the first Prime Minister of Japan.
events.html: • 1885 – Itō Hirobumi, a samurai, becomes the first Prime Minister of Japan.[16]

events.description: The Christmas Meeting of 1888, considered to be the official start of the Faroese independence movement.
events.html: • 1888 – The Christmas Meeting of 1888, considered to be the official start of the Faroese independence movement.[17]

events.description: Cornwallis Valley Railway begins operation between Kentville and Kingsport, Nova Scotia.
events.html: • 1890 – Cornwallis Valley Railway begins operation between Kentville and Kingsport, Nova Scotia.[18]

events.description: Asteroid 323 Brucia becomes the first asteroid discovered using photography.
events.html: • 1891 – Asteroid 323 Brucia becomes the first asteroid discovered using photography.[19]

events.description: The Dreyfus affair begins in France, when Alfred Dreyfus is wrongly convicted of treason.
events.html: • 1894 – The Dreyfus affair begins in France, when Alfred Dreyfus is wrongly convicted of treason.[20]

events.description: An Mw  7.9 earthquake strikes Xinjiang, China, killing at least 280.
events.html: • 1906 – An Mw  7.9 earthquake strikes Xinjiang, China, killing at least 280.[21]

events.description: The GOELRO economic development plan is adopted by the 8th Congress of Soviets of the Russian SFSR.
events.html: • 1920 – The GOELRO economic development plan is adopted by the 8th Congress of Soviets of the Russian SFSR.

events.description: Opening of Visva-Bharati College, also known as Santiniketan College, now Visva Bharati University, India.
events.html: • 1921 – Opening of Visva-Bharati College, also known as Santiniketan College, now Visva Bharati University, India.

events.description: The Lincoln Tunnel opens to traffic in New York City.
events.html: • 1937 – The Lincoln Tunnel opens to traffic in New York City.[22]

events.description: Indian Muslims observe a "Day of Deliverance" to celebrate the resignations of members of the Indian National Congress over their not having been consulted over the decision to enter World War II with the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1939 – Indian Muslims observe a "Day of Deliverance" to celebrate the resignations of members of the Indian National Congress over their not having been consulted over the decision to enter World War II with the United Kingdom.[23]

events.description: World War II: Himara is captured by the Greek army.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Himara is captured by the Greek army.

events.description: World War II: Adolf Hitler signs the order to develop the V-2 rocket as a weapon.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Adolf Hitler signs the order to develop the V-2 rocket as a weapon.

events.description: World War II: Battle of the Bulge: German troops demand the surrender of United States troops at Bastogne, Belgium, prompting the famous one word reply by General Anthony McAuliffe: "Nuts!"
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Battle of the Bulge: German troops demand the surrender of United States troops at Bastogne, Belgium, prompting the famous one word reply by General Anthony McAuliffe: "Nuts!"

events.description: World War II: The People's Army of Vietnam is formed to resist Japanese occupation of Indochina, now Vietnam.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The People's Army of Vietnam is formed to resist Japanese occupation of Indochina, now Vietnam.

events.description: U.S. President Harry S. Truman issues an executive order giving World War II refugees precedence in visa applications under U.S. immigration quotas.
events.html: • 1945 – U.S. President Harry S. Truman issues an executive order giving World War II refugees precedence in visa applications under U.S. immigration quotas.[24]

entities.name: World War II evacuation and expulsion

events.description: Sjafruddin Prawiranegara established the Emergency Government of the Republic of Indonesia (Pemerintah Darurat Republik Indonesia, PDRI) in West Sumatra.
events.html: • 1948 – Sjafruddin Prawiranegara established the Emergency Government of the Republic of Indonesia (Pemerintah Darurat Republik Indonesia, PDRI) in West Sumatra.[25]

entities.name: Emergency Government of the Republic of Indonesia

events.description: The cruise ship Lakonia burns 290 kilometres (180 mi) north of Madeira, Portugal with the loss of 128 lives.
events.html: • 1963 – The cruise ship Lakonia burns 290 kilometres (180 mi) north of Madeira, Portugal with the loss of 128 lives.[26]

events.description: The first test flight of the SR-71 (Blackbird) takes place at Air Force Plant 42 in Palmdale, California, United States.
events.html: • 1964 – The first test flight of the SR-71 (Blackbird) takes place at Air Force Plant 42 in Palmdale, California, United States.

events.description: In the United Kingdom, a 70 miles per hour (110 km/h) speed limit is applied to all rural roads including motorways for the first time.
events.html: • 1965 – In the United Kingdom, a 70 miles per hour (110 km/h) speed limit is applied to all rural roads including motorways for the first time.

events.description: Cultural Revolution: People's Daily posted the instructions of Mao Zedong that "The intellectual youth must go to the country, and will be educated from living in rural poverty."
events.html: • 1968 – Cultural Revolution: People's Daily posted the instructions of Mao Zedong that "The intellectual youth must go to the country, and will be educated from living in rural poverty."

events.description: The international aid organization Doctors Without Borders is founded by Bernard Kouchner and a group of journalists in Paris, France.
events.html: • 1971 – The international aid organization Doctors Without Borders is founded by Bernard Kouchner and a group of journalists in Paris, France.[27]

events.description: A Royal Air Maroc Sud Aviation Caravelle crashes near Tangier-Boukhalef Airport in Tangier, Morocco, killing 106.
events.html: • 1973 – A Royal Air Maroc Sud Aviation Caravelle crashes near Tangier-Boukhalef Airport in Tangier, Morocco, killing 106.[28]

entities.name: 1973 Royal Air Maroc Sud Aviation Caravelle crash

events.description: Grande Comore, Anjouan and Mohéli vote to become the independent nation of Comoros. Mayotte remains under French administration.
events.html: • 1974 – Grande Comore, Anjouan and Mohéli vote to become the independent nation of Comoros. Mayotte remains under French administration.

events.description: The house of former British Prime Minister Edward Heath is attacked by members of the Provisional IRA.
events.html: • 1974 – The house of former British Prime Minister Edward Heath is attacked by members of the Provisional IRA.

events.description: U.S. President Gerald Ford creates the Strategic Petroleum Reserve in response to the 1970s energy crisis.
events.html: • 1975 – U.S. President Gerald Ford creates the Strategic Petroleum Reserve in response to the 1970s energy crisis.[29]

events.description: The pivotal Third Plenum of the 11th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party is held in Beijing, with Deng Xiaoping reversing Mao-era policies to pursue a program for Chinese economic reform.
events.html: • 1978 – The pivotal Third Plenum of the 11th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party is held in Beijing, with Deng Xiaoping reversing Mao-era policies to pursue a program for Chinese economic reform.

entities.name: 11th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party

events.description: "Subway vigilante" Bernhard Goetz shoots four would-be muggers on a 2 express train in Manhattan section of New York, United States.
events.html: • 1984 – "Subway vigilante" Bernhard Goetz shoots four would-be muggers on a 2 express train in Manhattan section of New York, United States.[30]

events.description: In Zimbabwe, the political parties ZANU and ZAPU reach an agreement that ends the violence in the Matabeleland region known as the Gukurahundi.
events.html: • 1987 – In Zimbabwe, the political parties ZANU and ZAPU reach an agreement that ends the violence in the Matabeleland region known as the Gukurahundi.[31]

events.description: Romanian Revolution: Communist President of Romania Nicolae Ceaușescu is overthrown by Ion Iliescu after days of bloody confrontations. The deposed dictator and his wife Elena flee Bucharest in a helicopter as protesters erupt in cheers.
events.html: • 1989 – Romanian Revolution: Communist President of Romania Nicolae Ceaușescu is overthrown by Ion Iliescu after days of bloody confrontations. The deposed dictator and his wife Elena flee Bucharest in a helicopter as protesters erupt in cheers.[32]

events.description: German reunification: Berlin's Brandenburg Gate re-opens after nearly 30 years, effectively ending the division of East and West Germany.
events.html: • 1989 – German reunification: Berlin's Brandenburg Gate re-opens after nearly 30 years, effectively ending the division of East and West Germany.

events.description: Lech Wałęsa is elected President of Poland.
events.html: • 1990 – Lech Wałęsa is elected President of Poland.

events.description: Final independence of Marshall Islands and Federated States of Micronesia after termination of trusteeship.
events.html: • 1990 – Final independence of Marshall Islands and Federated States of Micronesia after termination of trusteeship.

entities.name: Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands

events.description: During approach to Tripoli International Airport, a Boeing 727 operating as Libyan Arab Airlines Flight 1103 collides in mid-air with a Libyan Air Force Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-23, killing 157 people.
events.html: • 1992 – During approach to Tripoli International Airport, a Boeing 727 operating as Libyan Arab Airlines Flight 1103 collides in mid-air with a Libyan Air Force Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-23, killing 157 people.[33]

events.description: Airborne Express Flight 827 crashes in Narrows, Virginia, killing all six people on board.
events.html: • 1996 – Airborne Express Flight 827 crashes in Narrows, Virginia, killing all six people on board.[34]

events.description: Acteal massacre: Attendees at a prayer meeting of Roman Catholic activists for indigenous causes in the small village of Acteal in the Mexican state of Chiapas are massacred by paramilitary forces.
events.html: • 1997 – Acteal massacre: Attendees at a prayer meeting of Roman Catholic activists for indigenous causes in the small village of Acteal in the Mexican state of Chiapas are massacred by paramilitary forces.

events.description: Somali Civil War: Hussein Farrah Aidid relinquishes the disputed title of President of Somalia by signing the Cairo Declaration, in Cairo, Egypt. It is the first major step towards reconciliation in Somalia since 1991.
events.html: • 1997 – Somali Civil War: Hussein Farrah Aidid relinquishes the disputed title of President of Somalia by signing the Cairo Declaration, in Cairo, Egypt. It is the first major step towards reconciliation in Somalia since 1991.

events.description: Just after taking off from London Stansted Airport, Korean Air Cargo Flight 8509 crashes into Hatfield Forest near Great Hallingbury, killing all four people on board.
events.html: • 1999 – Just after taking off from London Stansted Airport, Korean Air Cargo Flight 8509 crashes into Hatfield Forest near Great Hallingbury, killing all four people on board.[35]

events.description: Burhanuddin Rabbani, political leader of the Northern Alliance, hands over power in Islamic State of Afghanistan to the interim government headed by President Hamid Karzai.
events.html: • 2001 – Burhanuddin Rabbani, political leader of the Northern Alliance, hands over power in Islamic State of Afghanistan to the interim government headed by President Hamid Karzai.

events.description: Richard Reid attempts to destroy a passenger airliner by igniting explosives hidden in his shoes aboard American Airlines Flight 63.
events.html: • 2001 – Richard Reid attempts to destroy a passenger airliner by igniting explosives hidden in his shoes aboard American Airlines Flight 63.

events.description: An ash dike ruptured at a solid waste containment area for a Tennessee Valley Authority coal-fired power plant in Roane County, Tennessee, releasing 4.2 million m3 (1.1 billion US gal) of coal fly ash slurry in the largest industrial spill in U.S. history.
events.html: • 2008 – An ash dike ruptured at a solid waste containment area for a Tennessee Valley Authority coal-fired power plant in Roane County, Tennessee, releasing 4.2 million m3 (1.1 billion US gal) of coal fly ash slurry in the largest industrial spill in U.S. history.[36]

entities.name: Kingston Fossil Plant coal fly ash slurry spill

events.description: The repeal of the Don't ask, don't tell policy, the 17-year-old policy banning homosexuals serving openly in the United States military, is signed into law by President Barack Obama.
events.html: • 2010 – The repeal of the Don't ask, don't tell policy, the 17-year-old policy banning homosexuals serving openly in the United States military, is signed into law by President Barack Obama.[37]

entities.name: Don't Ask, Don't Tell Repeal Act of 2010

events.description: Bashir Ahmad Bilour of Awami National Party and eight others are killed in a Pakistan Taliban bomber suicide attack in Dhaki Nalbandi area near Qissa Khwani Bazaar.
events.html: • 2012 – Bashir Ahmad Bilour of Awami National Party and eight others are killed in a Pakistan Taliban bomber suicide attack in Dhaki Nalbandi area near Qissa Khwani Bazaar.[38]

events.description: A study finds the VSV-EBOV vaccine against the Ebola virus between 70 and 100% effective, thus making it the first proven vaccine against the disease.
events.html: • 2016 – A study finds the VSV-EBOV vaccine against the Ebola virus between 70 and 100% effective, thus making it the first proven vaccine against the disease.

events.description: United Nations Security Council Resolution 2397 against North Korea is unanimously approved.
events.html: • 2017 – United Nations Security Council Resolution 2397 against North Korea is unanimously approved.

events.description: President Donald Trump signs the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017.
events.html: • 2017 – President Donald Trump signs the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017.[39]

entities.name: Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017

events.description: A tsunami caused by an eruption of Anak Krakatau in Indonesia kills at least 430 people and injures almost a thousand more.
events.html: • 2018 – A tsunami caused by an eruption of Anak Krakatau in Indonesia kills at least 430 people and injures almost a thousand more.

events.description: The 2018–2019 United States federal government shutdown, the longest shutdown of the U.S. federal government in history, begins.
events.html: • 2018 – The 2018–2019 United States federal government shutdown, the longest shutdown of the U.S. federal government in history, begins.[40]

entities.name: Government shutdowns in the United States
